RM  9492329
RT  Structural determination of the O-antigenic polysaccharide from the
RT  enterotoxigenic Escherichia coli O147.
RA  Hygge Blakeman K, Weintraub A, Widmalm G;
RL  Eur J Biochem. 1998;251:534-537.
CC  The E. coli O147 antigen is a linear tetrasaccharide with the structure
CC  [->2)aLRha(1->2)aLRha(1->4)bDGalA(1->3)bDGalNAc(1->]. The Shigella
CC  flexneri O6 antogen is identical except for an additional 3-O-linked
CC  acetyl group on the second rhamnose [1]. Despite requiring three
CC  glycosidic linkages in the monomer unit, there are only two
CC  glycosyltransferases in the antigen biosynthesis cluster. The WfbY
CC  transferase is most closely related (32% identical) to WvwB from the
CC  O146 cluster, which is purported to transfer L-rhamnose in two
CC  different positions. WfbZ, on the other hand, is most closely related
CC  to a series of Gal->GalNAc transferases.
